{"id":74791,"title":"Improving dementia care through behavioral interventions.","abstract":"Behavioral interventions are effective in treating neuropsychiatric symptoms of dementia, yet older adults with dementia who require long-term care lack consistent access to caregivers who are skillful in selecting and applying these interventions. This commentary describes national and state-level initiatives that can improve access to effective behavioral techniques. ","date":"2014-09-20","categories":"Nervous System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25237882","annotations":[{"name":"Behavior","weight":0.740915,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavior"},{"name":"Symptom","weight":0.558165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symptom"},{"name":"Dementia","weight":0.31207,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dementia"},{"name":"Caregiver","weight":0.145536,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caregiver"},{"name":"Behavior modification","weight":0.0575019,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavior_modification"},{"name":"Neuropsychiatry","weight":0.0549849,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuropsychiatry"},{"name":"Consistency","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consistency"},{"name":"Intervention (counseling)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intervention_(counseling)"},{"name":"Old age","weight":0.0159005,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_age"},{"name":"Criticism","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Criticism"}]}
